The Finance Ministry is likely to allowJapanese financial institutions here to use overseas financialfutures market from next month, bond market sources said.    A senior ministry official declined to give an exacttiming, but said he expects removal of the ban on trading inoverseas financial futures as soon as possible.    The domestic call for participation in overseas markets tohedge foreign securities holding risks was reinforced by thelaunch of a night trading session by the Chicago Board of Tradefrom April 30. The session covers morning trading hours inTokyo.    Resident financial institutions are currently not allowedto participate in foreign financial futures markets, althoughtheir overseas branches may.    The newly eligible institutions are expected to besecurities houses, banks, life insurance companies andinvestment trusts, the market sources said. But the ministry islikely to prohibit broking business by those institutions andby individuals, the sources said.    In addition corporate investors are expected to be barredinitially because of their relative lack of experience. REUTER&#3;